      <p>The easy part is the report; the work that earns the fee is the judgment on top of it &mdash; building the forecast, modeling the pricing or the raise, framing the cash strategy, and sitting in the room when the decision gets made. Our advisory practice does that part-time, on a written scope and a fixed fee, on a foundation of accurate, closed books &mdash; and if the books aren&rsquo;t there yet, we say so before scoping anything. This is advisory work, not a regulated audit or assurance, and it&rsquo;s not a substitute for your CPA: the models inform your decisions, and the final call stays with you. Independent firm &mdash; not Intuit, and not Intuit&rsquo;s software support.</p>
